[Discovering sporadic cases of HPAI in very small holdings underlines
the level of alertness in Japan. As seen during 2003's HPAI in the
Netherlands, small holdings and hobby birds may become a significant
obstacle on the road to
complete disease eradication.
For updated (5 Mar 2004) information on the H5N1 situation in China,
Indonesia and Thailand, as well as on the H7 situation in Pakistan,
the reader is referred to the OIE web-site
<http://www.oie.int/downld/AVIAN%20INFLUENZA/A_AI-Asia.htm>
Results of the laboratory investigations, in particular, data on the
influenza strain involved, are anticipated. - Mod.AS]
